rlm-gh-fork

Ensure the current GitHub repository is forked under your account and
wire up the conventional remotes. Resolves the upstream (open source)
repo from the current checkout — if the checkout is already your fork,
its parent is treated as upstream; otherwise the repo itself is the
upstream. Checks via 'gh' whether a fork already exists under your
account and creates one if not. On completion the 'upstream' remote
points to the open source repo and 'origin' points to your fork.

It also runs 'gh repo set-default <upstream>' so that 'gh pr create'
targets the open source repo as the PR base while pushing your head
branch to your fork (origin). Without a default repo, 'gh' refuses to
pick one once two remotes exist.

Idempotent: running it again when the fork already exists only re-wires
the remotes. Refuses to act if a same-named repo exists under your
account that is not a fork, or is a fork of a different parent.

The clone protocol (ssh vs https) for the remote URLs follows your
'gh config get git_protocol' setting (defaults to https).

ENVIRONMENT
  None.

REQUIRES
  gh (authenticated via 'gh auth login'), git.
